\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"event\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"Evening Standard\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourprivacy notice.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourprivacy notice\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last autumnwe published a columnby the design and architecture writer Caz Facey who warned thatPariswas rapidly becoming more fashionable thanLondon.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delroy_Facey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Facey\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delroy_Facey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Delroy_Facey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Last autumnwe\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"a columnby\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"the design and architecture writer\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being a staunch defender of our city, I obviously pooh-poohed this (even though I published her annoyingly well-argued piece), and told her she was being hysterical.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 759, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a staunch defender\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"our city\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"her annoyingly well-argued piece\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When my daughter Georgia read it, she agreed with Caz, reiterating her complaint that while Paris was a proper 24-hour party city (her boyfriend lives there, so she spends a lot more time there than I do), London was becoming suburban, going to be in bed soon after midnight.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.815796911941316, \"rank\": 0.22390221117619677, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4863083811382293e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my daughter\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"Caz\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 814}, {\"ngram\": \"her complaint\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"a proper 24-hour party city\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"her boyfriend\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot more time\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"bed\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"midnight\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having always found Paris quite bourgeois and stubbornly old-fashioned, I did not pay either of them any mind.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"either\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"any mind\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But just last week, Londonlost its crown as Europe's most talked-about city onlineand on social media with Paris taking the top spot for the first time.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"But just last week, Londonlost\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"its crown\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1189}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe's most talked-about city onlineand\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"the top spot\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The growing excitement aroundthe build-up to the summer Olympic Gamesin the French capital obviously helped knock London off its perch at the top of the rankings of 60 cities, which have been compiled since 2018.\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1379, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9973002032932481, \"rank\": 0.0026483407055948346, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1417, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4863083811382293e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The growing excitement\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"aroundthe build-up\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Gamesin\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1374}, {\"ngram\": \"its perch\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"the rankings\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"60 cities\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as the Olympics, which kick off on July 26, Paris's profile has been raised by theRugby World Cuplast October and - bizarrely - by Fashion Week last September.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1568, \"end\": 1573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"theRugby World Cuplast October\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"Fashion Week\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sixth edition of the Europe's Most Talked About Cities report, compiled by digital communications agency ING Media, found that mentions of Paris grew 21 per cent last year compared with just four per cent for London.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4863083811382293e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sixth edition\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"Cities\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"report\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"digital communications agency ING Media\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \"mentions\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"21 per cent\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"just four per cent\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris itself is alive - busy, 'up', and full of people who look like they were happy with their lot The day after this was announced, I was actually in Paris myself, having lunch with my daughter and her boyfriend Max.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2061, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2123, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"score\": 0.9999999204869741, \"rank\": 7.594077024815988e-08, \"text\": \"Max\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Branning\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"their lot\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"lunch\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"my daughter\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"her boyfriend\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2119}, {\"ngram\": \"Max\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When she asked where I'd like to eat, I suggested somewhere that maybe served humble pie, although also somewhere with suitably notional service.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"humble pie\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"suitably notional service\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"True to form, she ignored me and we ended up in a brilliant place just behindGare du Nord.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brilliant place\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris itself was alive - busy, \\\"up\\\", and full of people who looked like they were happy with their lot.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"their lot\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We obviously made an obligatory stop in Merci, and spent some time looking at the galleries and bookshops in the Marais (sooo trendy now).\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2582, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Marais\", \"score\": 0.9999999976371328, \"rank\": 2.362858799729726e-09, \"text\": \"Marais\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Marais\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Marais\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an obligatory stop\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"Merci\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"some time\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2535}, {\"ngram\": \"the galleries\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2560}, {\"ngram\": \"bookshops\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So as I walked to theEurostar, I was contemplating having to modify my relationship with Paris, when I was confronted by a queue which was almost as long as the width of Gare du Nord itself.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2698, \"end\": 2703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0438419327759435e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theEurostar\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"my relationship\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"a queue\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2737}, {\"ngram\": \"the width\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"Gare\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"Nord\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ah, I muttered to myself, Paris!\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having got used to apologising to any visitors from Japan, China, Germany, Austria or Switzerland about Britain's systemically appalling transport system (which seems to go from bad to worse on a daily basis), it was nice to be reminded that the Parisian end of Eurostar is an absolute shambles.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 3128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2885, \"end\": 2890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.7466631703093511, \"rank\": 0.3377140019769897, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2892, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9745505572085826, \"rank\": 0.014738695126359612, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2899, \"end\": 2906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.6384515057794226, \"rank\": 0.5624431118603573, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9999990493006379, \"rank\": 8.568526856591395e-07, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}, {\"begin\": 2919, \"end\": 2930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999899196155, \"rank\": 1.0080102857665956e-08, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 3.945286802383707e-12, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8978704962063855e-15, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any visitors\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"a daily basis\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parisian end\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3091}, {\"ngram\": \"an absolute shambles\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While it was relatively easy to change our non-flexible ticket, the rest of the check-in process was a joke.\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our non-flexible ticket\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3192}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3202}, {\"ngram\": \"the check-in process\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3226}, {\"ngram\": \"a joke\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I had my passport inspected four times by four different people before I reached the automatic scanner, a process which also involved an especially officious border control person telling me they could not let me leave the country as my passport had too many stamps in it.\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my passport\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"four different people\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3302}, {\"ngram\": \"the automatic scanner\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3341}, {\"ngram\": \"a process\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"an especially officious border control person\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3418}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 3458, \"to\": 3469}, {\"ngram\": \"my passport\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3484}, {\"ngram\": \"too many stamps\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought that maybe they had employed so many people in order to ease the city's welfare budget, but surely the point of employing a multitude of people is to make things more efficient, not less so.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3712, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"so many people\", \"from\": 3551, \"to\": 3565}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3574}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's welfare budget\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"surely the point\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3630}, {\"ngram\": \"a multitude\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3665}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sacr\\u00e9 bleu!\", \"fro